      <div xml:id="KT217-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">uṭaṉpōkku nayappat tōḻi talaimakaṭkuk kūṟiyatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Spoken to HER by the confidante so that [she] would
          yield to going away together. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT217">
        <lg type="edition">

          <l>tiṉaikiḷi kaṭikeṉiṟ pakalu mollu</l>
          <l>miravunī varutali ṉūṟu mañcuval</l>
          <l>yāṅkuccey vāmem miṭumpai nōykkeṉa</l>
          <l>vāṅkiyāṉ kūṟiya vaṉaittiṟkup piṟitucet</l>
          <l>tōṅkumalai nāṭa ṉuyirttōṉ maṉṟa</l>
          <l>vaitē kāmam yāṉē</l>
          <l>kaḻimutuk kuṟaimaiyum paḻiyumeṉ ṟiciṉē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">

          <l>“If they said: "go chasing parakeets from the millet",</l>
          <l rend="indent6">it would be possible at midday too.</l>
          <l>Because of your coming at night, I fear obstacles too.</l>
          <l>What do we do against the pain that afflicts us?”</l>
          <l rend="indent3">When I spoke thus,</l>
          <l>he thought of another [thing to do] in such [a state of affairs],</l>
          <l>the man from the land of high mountains, [and] he sighed indeed:</l>
          <l>“desire is [all very] well!”</l>
          <l rend="indent8">But I,</l>
          <l>I said: “[this is] a very old short-cut, and [it is] blame.”</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
